# Execute full rules pass

When this file is referenced, run a **structured pass** against **`.cursor/rules/`** (numeric order), then **verify**, then **commit/push** only when the userÔÇÖs intent allows it.

## Scope (infer from the user)

| User intent | Apply | Skip or lighten |
|-------------|--------|-------------------|
| **Full repo** (default) | **`01` ÔåÆ `07`**, **`11-api-contracts`**, **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`** (tasks API / `pkgs/tasks` / related `web/src` + `DESIGN.md`), **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`** (`REPO_ROOT` / `pkgs/repo` / `/repo` / mention extensions), **`09`** (both files), **`10`** | ÔÇö |
| **Frontend then backend** (explicit user order) | **`10`**, **`09-local`**, **`09-security`**, then **`01` ÔåÆ `07`**, **`11`**, **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`** / **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`** if the matching stack changed, **`09`** | Same verification step at the end |
| **Backend / Go only** | **`01` ÔåÆ `07`**, **`11`**, **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`** (tasks API / store), **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`** (when changing `pkgs/repo` or `/repo` handlers), **`09`** | **`10-web-ui`** unless `web/` was touched |
| **Frontend / `web/` only** | **`10`**, **`09-local-verification`** (and **`09-security`** for secrets in client config) | Deep **`01`ÔÇô`07`** / **`11`** on Go only if Go files changed |
| **Audit / review, no commit** | Read and fix per rules; **do not** run **`08`** | Say explicitly: ÔÇ£audit-only; no commit.ÔÇØ |

If unclear, ask once: **full repo** vs **Go-only** vs **web-only**, **frontend-then-backend** vs default order, and whether to **commit and push** at the end.

## Phases

1. **Orient** ÔÇö Skim **`AGENTS.md`** (repo map, commands). List **`.cursor/rules/`**, sort by numeric prefix, skip **`00-*`** when *applying* (this file is the playbook, not a style rule).
2. **Substantive rules** ÔÇö In order **`01` ÔåÆ `07`**, then **`11-api-contracts`** (read the checklist when changing HTTP/SSE/JSON boundaries; on a full pass, skim to avoid drift), then **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`** when changing the tasks stack (routes, store, domain, audit/SSE, or task UI that hits the API; skip for trivial fixes), then **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`** when changing the workspace repo slice (`pkgs/repo`, `/repo/*`, `web/src/api/repo.ts`, mention extensions, or `REPO_ROOT` docs; skip for trivial fixes). Then **`09-security-baseline`** (light scan: secrets, unsafe logs), then **`09-local-verification`** (reminder: **`gofmt`**, **`go vet`**, tests), then **`10`** when `web/` is in scope. When editing root or `docs/*.md` prose, also apply **`12-documentation-style`**. For each: read ÔåÆ inspect ÔåÆ fix ÔåÆ run **targeted** tests for what you changed (do not run the full bar after every single edit). **`99-repo-primer`** is always-on context only, not a separate pass step.
3. **Verify** ÔÇö Once fixes for this pass are done, run the **full bar** once:
   - **`scripts/check.ps1`** (Windows) or **`scripts/check.sh`** (Unix) from repo root, **or** the equivalent: **`gofmt`** check / **`go fmt`**, **`go vet ./...`**, **`go test ./... -count=1`**, and (if `web/` changed) **`npm test`** + **`npm run build`** in **`web/`** (see **`09-local-verification.mdc`**).
   - **Recommended:** for meaningful behavior changes under **`pkgs/`** / **`internal/`**, run scoped coverage per **`06-testing.mdc`** and close obvious gaps (or note why not).
4. **Publish (rule `08`)** ÔÇö Only if there are changes to commit **and** the user did not ask for audit-only:
   - Apply **`08-atomic-commits`**: atomic commits, then **`git push`** (or set upstream), unless push is impossibleÔÇöreport outcome.
5. **Nothing to do** ÔÇö If the tree is clean and no rule required edits, say so briefly (no fake commits).

## Constraints

- Do not skip substantive rules unless **clearly not applicable** to the chosen scope.
- Do not move on with **failing** verification (`go vet`, `go test`, or `web/` build when in scope).
- **Batch commits at the end** of the pass per **`08`**; do not mix unrelated concerns in one commit.
- **Contradiction guard:** ÔÇ£Do not commit before the endÔÇØ means **do not commit mid-pass** while applying substantive rules (**`01`ÔÇô`07`**, **`11`**, **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`**, **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`**, **`09`**, **`10`**, **`12`** as applicable); the **end** of the pass is after verification, when **`08`** appliesÔÇöunless the user chose **audit-only**.

